headline: Git-for-data Pioneer lakeFS Secures $20M in Growth Capital, Fills a Critical Gap in Enterprise AI Tech Stack
summary: lakeFS, the leading "git-for-data" version control system for enterprise data and AI initiatives, has raised $20 million in a growth funding round. With thousands of organizations including Arm, Bosch, Lockheed Martin, NASA, Volvo, and the U.S. Department of Energy already using lakeFS as part of their data management infrastructure, this new investment will accelerate its growth supporting data engineering, AI and ML projects in the enterprise and public sector markets.
